      <arrangement id="aspace_deb8741379865e5e43a44494012aecdf">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_65e93a5fc2484aad11bc6d86dcf7a5e5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes, correspondence, reports, and personnel files documenting personnel, teaching appointments, curriculum, the American Numismatic Society, and the Board of Permanent Officers of the Yale Department of Classics.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5a7298679a52301b5056d7ef456d487f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>Some records in this finding aid have been redacted, as they include student names, donor names, and other restricted data. These records will not appear in the published finding aid.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
